$interpreted: Karen: Damn, nothing in this one...then what about that one?
Karen: Some people are willing to poach even at the risk of their lives. Money can truly make people sink into insanity.
Karen: Finally, found it! The Blazetail Lizard crystal!
Karen: Now that I've gotten the raw material. The next step is...
Sherlock: Hey, you! What are you trying to do to my family!?
Karen: ...What are you talking about?
Ned: Father, you're mistaken.
Lisa: President Karen asked us if we could let her go to the Kingdom of the Sun's coronation ceremony in place of us~
Sherlock: You're going to the coronation ceremony as well!?
Karen: As the President of the Desert Bazaar Chamber of Commerce, isn't it normal for me to visit the current ruler of the kingdom?
Sherlock: Hmph! I bet you're afraid that my magnificent presence is going to get me your position as president~
Sherlock: I'm taking Ned and Lisa, and that's that!
Lisa: But Ned and I both don't want to go〜
Ned: Those types of crowded places don't suit me. I'll feel much more at ease staying here in the desert.
Lisa: Well, if Ned's not going then I'm not either〜
Lisa: Plus. I don't really have much connection to the princess. I don't really know why I should be there to congratulate her.
Karen: Well, then it's settled. I'll go with you.
Sherlock: Rats! Then I'll go by myself. It doesn't matter what you say; I'm not taking you!
Karen: You troublesome tin can...here, take it.
Sherlock: Is this...a Blazetail Lizard crystal!?
Karen: Take a closer look.
Sherlock: Is this a real ruby?  A ruby this size is worth over a million Curren! And that's the bare minimum!
Sherlock: You...this...for me?
Karen: Not for you. It's a coronation gift for the Princess, a gift from the Chamber of Commerce as a whole. This way, you won't need to prepare another gift.
Karen: So, can I go?
Sherlock: Giving such a precious gift to that blonde brat is really quite a waste. It'd be better if you just give it to me.....
Karen: What did you just say?
Sherlock: I said...we set out in three days. Don't forget!
Karen: No problem.
